0 0 10 May  7 13:09:33 2026                    
Rule File Pathname: /home/user1/Desktop/ic/_SMIC_CalDRC_018LGMS_1833_V1.19_REV1_0.drc_
Space between two Mn regions when one or both Mn with 2-level continuous stacked via arrays (include TV) >= 1.0um.
1. DRC waive when metal edge encloses the stacked via array > 10um.
2. DRC only flag space violation region when Parallel run length >= 15um.
The continuous stacked via array definition:
1) Two vias whose space is <= 5um are considered to be in the same array, two via arrays with spacing <= 10um will be treated as one via array..
2) All via array overlapped width is >= 5um, and parallel run length >= 15um.
3) Each layer via density >= 1.66/um2,Top via density >=1.29/um2.
4) The vias in stacked via array interact with the same interlayer metal.
5) The 2-level continuous stacked via array means the stacked via array are 2 continuous via layers and the corresponding 1 interlayer metal has no metal cross (DRC waive width <= 2um metal line and check all interlayer metals projected space > 0um).
